Australia registered the second-biggest ODI Win.
Australia won by 309 runs, biggest World Cup win.
Key Match Events: Glenn Maxwell wins Man of the Match for the Fastest World Cup hundred.

Pre-Game Insights: Australia will face the Netherlands in the 24th match of the ICC Cricket World Cup, 2023 on October 25 at the Arun Jaitley Stadium in New Delhi, India.

South Africa has scored 428 runs on the same venue, which shows how good this surface is for the batters. The ball comes nicely onto the bat, and batters can play the shots on the up. Bowling will be challenging in the dew under the light, and it will be hard to grip the ball.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game between Australia and Netherlands will be available live on the Star Sports Networks. This will be available in regional languages as well. Fans who want the game in Tamil, Telugu, Malayalam, etc. can enjoy it on Star Sports channels. On the other hand, Disney+ Hotstar is another platform where cricket lovers can catch up on the live action on mobile phone and website.
